                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message">
                            <p><a title="Link: https://lgcommunity.us.com/profile/codymonster" href="https://lgcommunity.us.com/profile/codymonster" rel="nofollow">codymonster</a>, you can go to Settings &gt; All Settings &gt; General &gt; QuickStart + and turn off. Power off the TV and unplug the unit for 1 minute. This should restore the ability to connect to Wi-Fi. A replacement part isn't always needed, sometime straightening the Wi-Fi cable can help correct this problem. </p><p>We can get a service this corrected if you would like. Just message me your information. </p>                        </div>
